[{"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "FedEx is launching a new e-commerce platform as it competes with Amazon", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A person wheels several FedEx boxes on a handcart.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7NM9ouon8vFSb4w2hLfYzf2-tZw=/2x0:1199x798/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73054460/Courier_Boxes_13_003_04_02_02_242_160_110_11.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: FedEx</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Kv6phs\">FedEx announced that it will launch a new \u201cdata-driven commerce platform\u201d this fall called \u201cfdx\u201d that would put FedEx in the loop of every part of online sales, from purchases to delivery and returns. The platform will integrate with ShopRunner, an <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shoprunner.com%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F1%2F14%2F24038042%2Ffedex-fdx-e-commerce-platform-amazon-rival-shoprunner\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">online e-commerce store</a> the company <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/retailwire/20", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/14/24038042/fedex-fdx-e-commerce-platform-amazon-rival-shoprunner", "date_published": "2024-01-14T20:20:10+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "user": null, "language": "en", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Apple asks its San Diego Siri quality control team to relocate to Texas", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image of the Apple logo surrounded by gray, pink, and green outlines\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YT-GOvCK76xkoQLCp9HEcrCdnEg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73054215/VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_5_apple.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QQORyc\">Apple will combine a San Diego team of 121 employees with one in Austin, Texas, and any of the employees who elect not to move could be let go on April 26. That\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-01-14/apple-to-shutter-121-person-san-diego-ai-team-in-reorganization?sref=ExbtjcSG\">according to <em>Bloomberg</em></a>, which reported that an Apple spokesperson confirmed that the team, which listens to recordings of Siri interactions to make sure it responded appropriately, will \u201chave the opportunity to continue their role with Apple in Austin.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"A0tmG5\">The article reports that the st", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/14/24037904/apple-san-diego-siri-ai-team-relocating", "date_published": "2024-01-14T17:21:30+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": null, "album": "", "user": null, "language": "en", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Vision Pro demos will include scanning your glasses to identify your prescription", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Apple Vision Pro headset on display at Apple\u2019s headquarters in Cupertino.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_qfls1rMxa_L6zlSjxVYlm2J8as=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73054037/DSC00889.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hRrbS2\">For anyone who wants to try the Apple Vision Pro when it\u2019s officially released on February 2nd, there\u2019s going to be a whole <em>procedure</em>. We knew that, but now a report in Mark Gurman\u2019s <a href=\